node.text:
Captain Chelsey Sullenberger and First Officer Jeffery Skiles saved all 155 people onboard US Airways Flight 1549 after the successfully crash landing on the Hudson River in what would become to be known as the miracle on the Hudson. 

Video: @maxlangleyimages 
Media: Con Edison, AFP News, Live ATC Clips, Inc., AliasAnimo, Port Authority New York & New Jersey, ABC News, Wikimedia
Thumbnail: Carolinas Aviation Museum

node.text:
United Airlines (UA) has reached an agreement with the Air Line Pilots Association (ALPA) to prevent the furlough of close to 3,000 pilots. The deal has been agreed in principle and is still to be approved by the leadership of the ALPA UA chapter.

Link to article: https://airwaysmag.com/airlines/ua-pilots-union-agree-to-deal-avoid-furloughs/

Video: Max Langley (@maxlangleyimages)
Media: United Airlines
Thumbnail: Liam Funnell (@downwindaviation_)

📸 It's already time for another shot from the guys from @vhf_aviators

What a beautiful 787 shot it is as well!

"Winter has become our favorite time for plane spotting because of the exceptional light condition, especially no heat haze. This photo was taken at the end of 2020, and we decided to add a little bit of a warm tone to this photo to make the viewers feel comfortable when they look at it, also highlighted the aircraft. To be honest, we never regret going spotting on that day."

node.text:
📸 A new week means it's time for a new featured photographer. So, please welcome the guys from @vhf_aviators who will be sharing their great work with us this week!

"Hello guys, we are three aviation enthusiasts originally from Vietnam. One of us is currently studying in Canada, so you guys can see most of our photos are from Vancouver. 

Since we started plane spotting, we’ve had plenty of opportunities to catch exemplary shots of unique aircraft; however, this Air China’s Boeing 777-300ER is our favorite shot. 

Taken from the beginning of October 2020 when the weather in Vancouver started to get colder, you can see the snow started to cover the mountains at the back. Moreover, the great light condition that day has highlighted the beauty of the Triple Seven wearing the “Love China” livery."

If you would like to be our next Weekly Feature Photographer, use the #AirwaysMagazine hashtag or tag @airwaysmag in your photos for a chance to be featured! ✈️
